    "type": "Question",
    "name": "Question 62 @ 2018/2019",
    "Question": {
      "content": "Which of the following is not a main effect of an electric current?",
      "type": "OBJ",
      "options": [
        "magnetic effect",
        "chemical effect",
        "heating effect",
        "nuclear effect"
      ]
    },
    "Answer": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "nuclear effect"
    },
    "Explanation": {
      "type": "string",
      "content": "Electric currents primarily cause **heating** (Joule heating), **magnetic** (Oersted’s law), and **chemical** effects (electrolysis). Nuclear effects require interactions with atomic nuclei, not just charge flow."
    },
